comments.body:
@enku I think others can face this issue as well if they try to reuse the container which was created with older version but also I am not sure if its a good idea to treat build containers as stateful items so I am not sure if there's gonna be lot of cases like these.

But lets see maybe we can add this in troubleshooting docs. Interested in opening a PR for adding this into troubleshooting docs ?

I am closing this issue since problem is resolved for you.  But feel free to reopen if you see any issues again or continue discussion below.

@guystreeter if you have podman on board too, you could use the big hammer `podman system reset --force`.  Or the other big hammers:
`rm -rf /var/lib/containers/*` # for rootful
`rm -rf $HOME/.local/share/containers/*` # for rootless
